## Epic: Assessment Memo Email & Auto-Linking Integration

### E-INT-3: Assessment Memo Email Dispatch

**Business Objective:** When IC reaches ANALYSIS stage and assessment is required, investigator triggers email to revenue specialist with memo instructions. Revenue specialist completes assessment, replies to email, and reply auto-links back to IC.

#### US_INT-2.1-1: Design Assessment Memo Email Template & Send Logic

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Email template defined:
- Subject: “[IC-{IC_ID}] Assessment Memo Required – {Taxpayer_Name}”
- Body includes:
  - IC reference number (for reply detection)
  - Investigation summary (from IC.Investigation_Summary__c)
  - Memo instructions (link to assessment SOP)
  - Deadline: T+5 days (Assessment_Memo_Due_Date__c = sent_date + 5d)
  - Reply-to: investigations-assessments@[domain].gov.au
- Footer: “Do not modify the subject line; reply to this email with assessment attachment”
1. Send trigger: Investigator clicks “Send Assessment Memo” button on IC (or auto-triggered when IC.Assessment_Required__c = TRUE)
1. Recipient email address pulled from custom setting: Assessment_Specialist_Email__c (configurable)
1. Email sent via SF native email (not third-party service)
1. Investigation_Action_c event logged: type=MEMO_SENT, timestamp=NOW, recipient=email address

**Story Points:** 3

-----

#### US_INT-2.1-2: Configure Email-to-Case Mailbox & Auto-Linking

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Salesforce Email-to-Case mailbox configured:
- Mailbox address: investigations-assessments@[domain].gov.au
- Support email address configured in SF
1. Email routing rules configured:
- Emails with subject containing “[IC-” are captured
- IC reference extracted from subject (regex: [IC-(\d+)])
- Auto-linked to IC record using IC ID
1. Assessment email replies auto-create EmailMessage records linked to IC
1. Email attachment (assessment PDF, Excel) stored as Case File attachment (Salesforce Files)
1. Testing: send test assessment memo, verify reply auto-links to IC

**Story Points:** 5

-----

#### US_INT-2.1-3: Implement Assessment Memo Non-Response Escalation (5-Day SLA)

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Custom fields on IC:
- assessment_memo_sent_date__c (set when memo sent)
- assessment_memo_due_date__c (calculated = sent_date + 5 days, configurable via custom setting Assessment_Memo_SLA_Days__c)
- assessment_memo_response_received__c (checkbox, set TRUE when email reply detected)
- assessment_memo_status__c (picklist: Pending, Received, Overdue, Escalated)
1. Scheduled Apex job: “Assessment Memo SLA Monitor” runs daily at 00:15 UTC
- Query: IC records where assessment_memo_due_date__c < TODAY AND assessment_memo_response_received__c = FALSE AND assessment_memo_status__c != ‘Received’
- For each overdue memo:
  a. Set assessment_memo_status__c = ‘Overdue’
  b. Create Task:
  - Title: “Assessment Memo Non-Response – IC-{IC_ID}”
  - Assigned to: IC.OwnerId (Investigator)
  - Due Date: TODAY + 1 day (Escalation_Response_SLA_Days__c configurable)
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Description: “Revenue specialist did not respond to assessment memo sent on {sent_date}. Follow up immediately. Contact {revenue_specialist_email} or escalate to supervisor.”
    c. Log Investigation_Action_c event: type=MEMO_NO_RESPONSE, timestamp=NOW, days_overdue=TODAY-due_date
    d. Flag case in C8 dashboard: “Blocked on Assessment”
1. Optional: If Task not closed by {due_date + 3 days}, auto-escalate to Program Lead (Investigation_Program_Lead_Escalation_Days__c configurable)
1. Configuration stored in Assessment_Memo_SLA__c custom setting:
- Assessment_Memo_SLA_Days__c (default: 5)
- Escalation_Response_SLA_Days__c (default: 1)
- Enable_Auto_Escalation_to_PL__c (default: TRUE)
- Program_Lead_Escalation_Days__c (default: 3)

**Story Points:** 8

-----

#### US_INT-2.1-4: Implement Assessment Response Population (Assessment Liability)

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. When email reply is auto-linked to IC:
- Email attachment (assessment PDF or Excel with calculated liability) is stored as Case File
- Revenue specialist provides assessment in email body or attachment (assessment_liability_c value)
1. Process: Investigator or system extracts liability value from email/attachment:
- Manual: Investigator enters Assessment_Liability__c on IC (case-sensitive, required for exit letter generation)
- Auto (if possible): Parse email attachment for liability amount (may require OCR or fixed format)
1. Once Assessment_Liability__c populated:
- assessment_memo_response_received__c = TRUE
- assessment_memo_status__c = ‘Received’
- assessment_memo_response_date__c = email received date
- Investigation_Action_c event logged: type=ASSESSMENT_COMPLETED
1. Trigger IC state transition: INVESTIGATING → ASSESSMENT_RECEIVED (if assessment was required)
1. Next step: case proceeds to FINALIZING_EXIT state (merge assessment into exit letter)

**Story Points:** 5

