## Epic: Batch Processes & Scheduled Jobs

### E-INT-11: Daily SLA Monitoring & Escalation Batch

**Objective:** Consolidated batch job for all daily SLA checks (T+7 warning, T+10 hard stop, entry letter SLA, assessment memo SLA, objection window).

#### US_INT-6.1-1: Implement Consolidated SLA Batch Job

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Scheduled Apex batch job: “Daily_SLA_Monitor” scheduled daily at 00:30 UTC (after PIC → IC APIs quiet)
1. Single batch processes all IC records:
- Check T+7 evidence deadline (send warning if TODAY)
- Check T+10 evidence hard stop (block progression if TODAY + incomplete)
- Check entry letter SLA (alert if allocated >1d without letter)
- Check assessment memo SLA (create escalation task if >5 days without response)
- Check objection window Day 55 (send reminder if deadline is in 5 days)
- Check 60-day objection window expiration (auto-close case if deadline reached)
1. Batch processes max 200 records per invocation (Salesforce limit)
1. Logs all actions to Investigation_Action_c
1. Failure handling: if batch fails, email SF admin with error details + retry count

