## Epic: Integration Testing & Deployment

### E-INT-12: Integration Test Strategy

#### US_INT-7.1-1: Define Integration Test Scenarios

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Happy path scenarios:
- PIC created in ESYS → IC created in SF (verify all fields mapped)
- Investigator sends assessment memo → revenue specialist replies → auto-link to IC (verify attachment linked, liability populated)
- Customer uploads evidence via portal → auto-linked to IC (verify file stored, receipt logged)
- Entry letter sent → dispatched by Comms System → confirmation received (verify SLA met)
- Exit letter approved → dispatched → objection window started (verify 60-day timer begins)
- Objection received → IC re-investigation triggered (verify status transition)
- 60-day window expires → IC closed → PIC closed in ESYS (verify both systems updated)
1. Failure scenarios:
- PIC → IC API fails 3 times → alert + manual retry
- Assessment memo non-response >5 days → escalation task created
- Portal file >20MB → rejected with error to user
- TRIM folder path invalid → validation error, save blocked
- Exit letter dispatch fails → alert + manual retry
- IC close API fails → alert + Program Lead manual close override
1. Edge cases:
- Multiple PICs for same taxpayer → verify each gets separate IC
- Objection received on Day 60 (last day) → verify accepted
- Objection received on Day 61 → verify rejected (outside window)
- Assessment memo reply with no attachment → verify investigator must manually enter liability

**Story Points:** 5

-----

#### US_INT-7.1-2: Implement Integration Test Suite (Apex)

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Apex test classes created for each integration:
- TestPICToICAPI: mock ESYS API call, verify IC created with correct fields
- TestICCloseAPI: mock Salesforce close trigger, verify API call to ESYS
- TestAssessmentMemoEmail: mock email send + reply auto-link
- TestPortalEvidenceUpload: mock file upload, verify Salesforce Files created
- TestEntryLetterDispatch: mock Comms System call, verify letter SLA gate
- TestExitLetterDispatch: mock Comms System call, verify objection window started
1. Each test class covers:
- Happy path (95%+ coverage)
- Error handling (400, 500 responses)
- Boundary conditions (max file size, SLA edge cases)
1. Test coverage: >85% of integration code
1. Tests documented with comments explaining expected behavior

**Story Points:** 13

-----

#### US_INT-7.1-3: Implement Manual Testing & UAT Checklist

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. UAT test cases created (spreadsheet format):
- Manual test steps for each integration scenario (happy path + failure)
- Test data prep: sample PICs in ESYS, test portal users, test Comms System endpoints
